What You Can Do For Free (Non-Commercial Use)

You are free to use this framework at no cost for non-commercial purposes, including:

Internal evaluation, experimentation, or pilots

Internal process improvement or governance

Internal employee training or education

Academic, research, or nonprofit use

Reading, studying, theorizing, or discussing the framework

Internal organizational planning

You do not need permission for the above.

Attribution Requirement

If you use or adapt the material in any way (even internally), appropriate credit must be given.

Required attribution wording:

“Based on the Kaizen AI Integration Model created by Nathan Rudloff.”

What You Cannot Do For Free (Commercial Use)

Commercial use is NOT permitted under the Creative Commons license.

“Commercial use” includes (but is not limited to):

Using the framework in paid consulting, client services, or deliverables

Including it in proposals, bids, or sales processes

Charging for training, certification, or workshops using this framework

Embedding or integrating it into any paid product, platform, or service

Using it in corporate, enterprise, or revenue-generating operations

Redistributing or sublicensing for compensation

If money changes hands and this framework is part of the value,
that is commercial use.

Commercial Licensing Options

Commercial use of this framework requires a paid license issued by the author.

Organizations have two options:

1) Perpetual Commercial License

One-time payment of $50,000 USD

Permanent commercial rights

Non-exclusive

Non-transferable without written approval

2) 1-Year Commercial License

$5,000 USD

Valid for 12 months from date of agreement

Non-exclusive

Non-transferable

Renewable annually upon payment

Commercial use includes any paid, client-facing, revenue-generating, proposal, delivery, training, resale, or service use of this framework.

A commercial license is only valid when executed through a written agreement signed by the author, Nathan Rudloff.
Use of this material in any commercial capacity without such a license is not authorized.

